Manuall installation steps for ros2 and ros_micro_agent on jetson

ros2 installation on jetson:

1. 

sudo apt update && sudo apt install locales -y
sudo locale-gen en_US en_US.UTF-8
sudo update-locale LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8 LANG=en_US.UTF-8
export LANG=en_US.UTF-8


2. To verify run:

locale

Should show LANG=en_US.UTF-8

3. Add ROS2 APT repository:

sudo apt install software-properties-common -y
sudo add-apt-repository universe
sudo apt update && sudo apt install curl gnupg2 lsb-release -y


4. Now add the ROS 2 key and source:

sudo curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ros/rosdistro/master/ros.key -o /usr/share/keyrings/ros-archive-keyring.gpg

echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/ros-archive-keyring.gpg] http://packages.ros.org/ros2/ubuntu $(lsb_release -sc) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ros2.list > /dev/null


5. Install ROS2 Foxy minimal setup:

sudo apt install ros-foxy-ros-base -y

sudo apt install ros-foxy-demo-nodes-cpp -y
sudo apt install ros-foxy-demo-nodes-py -y


6. Soruce the ROS2 environment:

echo "source /opt/ros/foxy/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc


7. Install Development Tools (Optional):

sudo apt install -y python3-colcon-common-extensions python3-argcomplete build-essential


8. Verify Installation

Run a simple ROS 2 talker/listener demo:

Terminal 1:

ros2 run demo_nodes_cpp talker


Terminal 2:

ros2 run demo_nodes_cpp listener


You should see messages like:

[INFO] [talker]: Publishing: 'Hello World: 1'
[INFO] [listener]: I heard: [Hello World: 1]



For mirco_ros_agent installation on jetson:

1. Ensure ROS 2 Foxy is properly sourced
source /opt/ros/foxy/setup.bash

2. Install required dependencies

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3-pip python3-colcon-common-extensions git build-essential

3. Create Workspace for agent:

mkdir -p ~/microros_ws/src
cd ~/microros_ws/src

4. Clone the micro-ROS Agent repository

git clone -b foxy https://github.com/micro-ROS/micro-ROS-Agent.git
git clone -b foxy https://github.com/micro-ROS/micro-ROS-msgs.git


5. Return to your workspace root and build:

cd ~/microros_ws
colcon build

6. Source the workspace:

source install/setup.bash


To make it permanent:

echo "source ~/microros_ws/install/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc


